The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 All morning flights from the city on Thursday morning were delayed due to fog. Officials said no domestic flight could take off from Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport till 7.20 am. The first to leave was a Port Blair-bound Alliance Air flight.

 The Council for Indian School Certificate Examinations will allow disabled children to use computers for writing the ICSE (Class X) and ISC (Class XII) exams. The students will be able to avail of the facility from 2006, Rita Wilson, deputy secretary of the council, said on Thursday. Visually-challenged students will have the opportunity to use Braille keyboards. 

 Manoranjan Golui, 57, who worked as a guard at a school in Salt Lake, committed suicide on Wednesday night. He jumped off a three-storeyed building in the Baisakhi housing estate, in Salt Lake. He was rushed to hospital, where doctors pronounced him dead. Officers of Bidhannagar (North) police station said Golui had been suffering from depression.

 Shamsul Alam, 55, a Bangladeshi national, was found dead in a hotel on SN Banerjee Road on Thursday morning. The hotel authorities informed police after repeated knocks on Alam?s door failed to elicit a response. The cops broke open the door and found Alam unconscious on the bed. He was taken to NRS Medical College and Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. Police said no injury mark was found on the body. 

 A 45-year old man, suffering from tuberculosis, committed suicide on Thursday morning. Shankar Das was found hanging from the ceiling of his house in Bijpur, near Barrackpore.

 Rik Debnath, 5, went missing from his residence in Behala on Thursday afternoon. As his sandals were found on the banks of a pond nearby, Rik?s parents feared he might have drowned. Neighbours scoured the tank but could not recover the body. 

 Power supply to consumers in Putiary, Kudghat, Golf Green, Moore Avenue, Chandi Ghosh Road, Ranikuthi, Khanpur, Sree Colony, Gandhi Colony, Regent Park, Raipur, Pallysree Colony, Netaji Nagar, Bijoygarh, Bansdroni, Naktala, Baisnabghata, Garia and Bagha Jatin areas may be affected between 10 am and 3 pm on Friday. CESC will carry out maintenance work at a transformer in Tollygunge. 

 Vivek Sau, 4, was found dead in front of a house on Tollygunge Road at 10 pm on Wednesday. The face bore several injury marks. Police took Vivek to MR Bangur Hospital, where doctors pronounced him dead. His parents said he was last seen playing in front of their home around 8.30 am.

 The Metro Railway authorities received a hoax call at 11.15 am on Thursday that a bomb had been kept at Metro Bhavan, off Park Street, which would explode at 2.30 pm. Anuj Sharma, deputy commissioner of police (headquarters), said a bomb disposal squad had searched the entire building, but found nothing.

 A fast-track court in Baruipur, on the southern fringes of the city, convicted six persons of murdering schoolteacher Ranjit Das. The verdict, delivered on Thursday by Rabindra Nath Samanta, acquitted four others named in the FIR. Das was murdered on Kali puja night in 2003 for asking members of a local club not to play loudspeakers.

